quote: Individualsm is a fatal poison. But individuality is the salt of common life.
Certain defects are necessary for the existence of individuality.
In a society that tries to standardize thinking, individuality is not highly prized.
Individualsm is a fatal poison. But individuality is the salt of common life.
Certain defects are necessary for the existence of individuality.
In a society that tries to standardize thinking, individuality is not highly prized.
No one can transcend their own individuality.
No one should part with their individuality and become that of another.
What ever crushes individuality is despotism, no matter what name it is called.
What is genius but the power of expressing a new individuality?
